The Multi-Agent RLRM (Reinforcement Learning with Reward Machines) Framework is a library designed to facilitate the formulation of multi-agent problems and solve them through reinforcement learning. The model integrates 252,056 field records from 18,004 sites across China to build a multi-source datadriven machine learning framework for wheat yield prediction. Mapping Alternate Scenarios of Forest Intactness (MASFI) is a cloud-based machine learning framework. It uses XGBoost regression and remote sensing data such as GEDI LiDAR to create high-resolution maps and statistics, supporting protected area planning and management.
